				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Any clues why this irq handler isn't working?  The y scrolling doesn't seem to work at all in JNes, Nestopia, and FCEUX in the irq handler. (triggered by mmc3)
<br />
<br />However, in JNes and FCEUX the X scrolling is working, so the interrupt does function. 
<br />
<br />I'm wondering if the emulators are fubar, or there is something else I need to be doing.
<br />
<br />Thanks,
<br />Crash
<br />
<br />PPU_STAT  = $2002 ; Can be read to get current PPU status
<br />PPU_SCRL  = $2005 ; Sets X/Y scrolling of background
<br />MMC3_IRQ_ACK     = $E000  ;scanline IRQ acknowledge/disable
<br />
<br />;variable locations
<br />R_SCRX = $02
<br />R_SCRY = $03
<br />
<br />
<br />irq:
<br />	pha	;push a
<br />	txa
<br />	pha	;push x
<br />	tya
<br />	pha	;push y
<br />
<br />	ldx #0	
<br />	stx MMC3_IRQ_ACK
<br />
<br />	ldx PPU_STAT	;read to prime cpu scroll
<br />	lda R_SCRX		
<br />	sta PPU_SCRL
<br />	lda R_SCRY	
<br />	sta PPU_SCRL	
<br />	
<br />
<br />	pla
<br />	tay	;pull y
<br />	pla
<br />	tax	;pull X
<br />	pla	;pull a
<br />
<br />    rti</div>

