						<div class="postbody">Yes, you can't do sprite multiplexing as you can on the Commodore64, and also you can't acess to VRAM directly as you can on the Commodore, you have to do it during VBlank. However, the graphics the NES have to offer are overall better, and 64 small sprites is infinitely better than 8 limited huge sprites.</div>

					
